  "texts": [
    "Observing simulated children, we will monitor two competencies: Linguistic Ability: We are interested in how the language model can adapt the complexity of linguistic expression to match the presumed abilities of the simulated speaker.",
    "We test the ability of the simulated personas to simulate the mental states of other entities.",
    "We chose the Theory of Mind (ToM) framework as an ideal candidate for the exploration of mental state understanding since it showcases pronounced age-related differences in performance, providing us with a gradient to study.",
    "Also, the performance in so-called falsebelief tasks (a common way of testing ToM) is well-studied and documented in the cognitive developmental literature (see, e.g., [7] for an overview).",
    "For both competencies, linguistic and cognitive, we anticipate a progressive increase of capabilities correlating with the increasing age of the simulated child personas."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
    "Also, the performance in so-called falsebelief tasks (a common way of testing ToM) is well-studied and documented in the cognitive developmental literature (see, e.g., [7] for an overview)."
